00:03:46.167 --> 00:03:49.750
one over one minus one
over three to the n.

00:03:50.951 --> 00:03:53.896
So we could say this is
the same thing as the limit

00:03:53.896 --> 00:03:58.063
as n approaches infinity
of one over one minus one,

00:03:59.824 --> 00:04:01.537
over three to the n.

00:04:01.537 --> 00:04:03.360
Well what's this going to be equal to?

00:04:03.360 --> 00:04:05.149
Well as that approaches
infinity, this thing,

00:04:05.149 --> 00:04:07.416
one over three to the n,
that's just gonna go to zero.

00:04:07.416 --> 00:04:10.994
So this is, this whole thing
is just going to approach one.

00:04:10.994 --> 00:04:14.330
And one is clearly
between zero and infinity,

00:04:14.330 --> 00:04:17.003
so the destinies of these
two series are tied.

00:04:17.003 --> 00:04:21.286
They either both converge
or they both diverge.

00:04:21.286 --> 00:04:25.315
So this is a good one to use
a limit comparison test with,

00:04:25.315 --> 00:04:26.177
and so let's think about it.

00:04:26.177 --> 00:04:29.809
Do they either both converge,
or do they both diverge?

00:04:29.809 --> 00:04:33.541
Well this is a geometric
series, our common ratio here

00:04:33.541 --> 00:04:37.336
is less than one, so this
is going to converge,

00:04:37.336 --> 00:04:38.750
this is going to converge.

00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:40.217
And because this one converges, by the

00:04:40.217 --> 00:04:45.031
limit comparison test, our
original series S converges.

00:04:45.031 --> 00:04:47.281
Converges, and we are done.

